headline.main: THE GREAT CRICKET MATCH.; Match Between the Eleven of England and Twenty-two of Canada--The Betting The Playground--The English PlayersParticulars of the Match--England Victorions--Dinner of the Montreal Cricket Club.

docs.lead_paragraph: The great cricket match between the Eleven of England and Twenty-two of Eastern Canada is, of course, the great subject of interest here, just now. Nobody talks or writes or dreams of anything but cricket, Bats are discussed at breakfast as freely as beefsteaks, and balls, at dinner, as often as if they were eatable. All the world is here. docs.lead_paragraph: The Galway steamer, touching at St. Johns, N. F., brings news two days later from Europe. The departure of the Great Eastern, from Holyhead, for Portland, was officially announced for Oct. 28. Almost simultaneously with this notice, the death of Mr. BRUNEL, the engineer, to whom the first conception of the noble vessel is due, has occurred, resulting from a stroke of paralysis.

headline.main: NEWS BY TELEGRAPH.; The Proposed Treaty with Mexico--Probable Transfer of the Negotiations to Washington--The British Emissary to the Island of San Juan--Miscellaneous News. INTERESTING FROM WASHINGTON.

docs.lead_paragraph: The private secretary of Senor LERDO left NewYork on Tuesday last, as bearer of dispatches from Senor MATA to his Government, via New-Orleans. This messenger expects to reach New-Orleans in time for the steamer of the 27th inst., arrive in Vera Cruz by the 3d of October, leave again on the British steamer of the 5th for Havana, and reach this city by the middle of October.

headline.main: OBITUARY.; Death of Prof. George Bush.

docs.lead_paragraph: The announcement of the death of Prof. GEORGE BUSH will not be a surprise to the friends of that distinguished gentleman; for his health had been rapidly failing, and it is but a few weeks since an unfounded rumor of his decease went abroad. Prof. BUSH died at Rochester on Monday, Sept. 19, in the 63d year of his age.
